DefaultPipelineStackOverride: Specifies a different pipeline stack for Interchange to use by default when importing specific types of assets.
ShowImportDialogOverride: This tell interchange if the import dialog should show or not when importing a particular type of asset.
PipelineStacks: Configures the pipeline stacks that are available when importing assets with Interchange.
DefaultPipelineStack: Specifies which pipeline stack Interchange should use by default.
ImportDialogClass: Specifies the class that should be used to define the configuration dialog that Interchange shows on import.
bShowImportDialog: If enabled, the import option dialog will show when interchange import or re-import.
